				<h3 class="tt-norms-bold" style="font-size: 24px;"> Electrical Engineer</h3>	
				<p> 
					Throughout my Electrical Engineering degree at Memorial University, I specialized in the Power stream, focusing on courses such as Electromechanical Devices, Rotating Machines, Power Electronics, and Renewable Energy Systems. My coursework provided a strong foundation in electrical power generation, transmission, and control, complemented by hands-on experience in industrial controls and supervisory data acquisition. Additionally, my capstone Electrical Engineering Design Project allowed me to apply my knowledge to real-world power applications, reinforcing my technical and analytical skills.
				</p>
				<div class="uk-h3">Swimming Instructor</div>
				<p>While at YMCA Belize, I embraced the challenge of becoming a swimming instructor despite not being a strong swimmer. My dedication and eagerness to learn new skills drove me to apply my training quickly and effectively. I went above and beyond to support my students, even earning heartfelt praise from a parent for my extra effort in helping a struggling learner. Committed to delivering the best instruction possible, I took the initiative to research innovative teaching techniques, ensuring that every student received the guidance they needed to succeed. This experience strengthened my adaptability and perseverance while reinforcing my passion for mentorship and skill development. </p>
